						<summary>

						<p>On the north wall of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the Bhaktajanēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Parakēsarivarman (Parāntaka I ?) Year 2: 909 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription may palaeographically be assigned to Parāntaka I's period.</p>						

						<p>It records the assignment of twenty-four <hi rend="italic">cheṟuvu</hi> of land out of twentyfive designated as <hi rend="italic">Iriṇīkkī Aḍaiyakoṉaṇkai cheṟuvu</hi> for the maintenance of five servants engaged for sweeping and cleaning the temple premises. The other remaining one <hi rend="italic">cheṟuvu</hi> had been set apart as maintenance for the one who was blowing the <hi rend="italic">kāḷam.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
